WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.480
You know what looks great? Your Shiny apps. And you know what looks even better? Your Shiny apps

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:09.040
at night with Dark Mode. I'm going to show you how you can easily add Dark Mode to Shiny for

00:00:09.040 --> 00:00:14.080
Python apps with three quick steps. Here I have a simple app with a histogram that reacts to an

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:19.920
input slider that's stored in a sidebar. So for the first step, I'm going to add UIInputDarkMode.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:26.480
This adds a toggle button that makes it easy for users to switch between light and dark mode.

00:00:26.480 --> 00:00:31.520
And in many apps, this is all you need. In my app, I'd like to be able to see the text of this plot.

00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:36.720
The second step is to give your Dark Mode button an ID. This lets you react to the current theme

00:00:36.720 --> 00:00:41.200
in your server logic. I've written plotHistogram so that it takes a foreground color, which is

00:00:41.200 --> 00:00:46.000
currently set to black. But now we can react to the current color mode and choose black if the

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:53.119
mode is light, otherwise silver. And just like that, we have an app that looks good by day or night.

